Usage: all_constraint_modes [-help] [-active  | -active_setup  | -active_hold ]

-help             # Prints out the command usage
-active           # Returns a list of the defined constraint modes associated
                  # with all active analysis views (bool, optional)
-active_hold      # Returns a list of the defined constraint modes associated
                  # with active hold analysis views only (bool, optional)
-active_setup     # Returns a list of the defined constraint modes associated
                  # with active setup analysis views only (bool, optional)